{"TopicId":149997,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.9.x] EVA Enhancements Continued","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T17:25:40Z","PageNum":3,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-20T17:40:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222961726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487606782\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169510\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jebs_SY\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jebs_SY said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, the log time switch can be seen \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.twitch.tv/videos/123308728?t=04h39m40s\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E. Navball is auto-open and was switching via Haystack, if this matters.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can observe further. Maybe is switching with haystack the / an issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing there is the navball, I\u0027ll add a check and get out an update this evening\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-20T22:58:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew release, 0.1.6\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nFixed nullref when switching to a scansat\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-01T00:51:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to make the nav ball follow the Kerbal position, not the camera?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stratvox","CreatedById":134498,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-06T00:18:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E, one thing that I think would make this way better is if it would be possible to enable \u0022Locked\u0022 camera mode when running on EVA with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E turned off (i.e. not automagically aligning the kerbal with the camera).\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EI have no idea if that\u0027s possible, but it occurs to me that would end up making the whole \u0022point vessel at orbital normal to enable easy (dis)embarking\u0022 moot.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ERight now when you cycle through the camera modes (with V) the closest you can get to this is \u0022Chase\u0022 but that still has the cameral viewing normal as up all the time.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EThoughts?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheers!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-06T03:33:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222971381\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488329477\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Teilnehmer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/28/2017 at 7:51 PM, Teilnehmer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to make the nav ball follow the Kerbal position, not the camera?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you saying it doesn\u0027t follow the kerbal now?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222977012\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488759520\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022134498\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022stratvox\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, stratvox said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E, one thing that I think would make this way better is if it would be possible to enable \u0022Locked\u0022 camera mode when running on EVA with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E turned off (i.e. not automagically aligning the kerbal with the camera).\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EI have no idea if that\u0027s possible, but it occurs to me that would end up making the whole \u0022point vessel at orbital normal to enable easy (dis)embarking\u0022 moot.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ERight now when you cycle through the camera modes (with V) the closest you can get to this is \u0022Chase\u0022 but that still has the cameral viewing normal as up all the time.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis may be more of a question for some of the camera mods, not sure. \u00A0Nothing I can do about this now, anyway, busy with some other issues\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-06T17:32:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222977165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488771216\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you saying it doesn\u0027t follow the kerbal now?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly. I experience the same navball behavior as in stock:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nWhen controlling a vessel, the navball doesn\u2019t follow the camera. It follows the vessel.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBut when controlling a Kerbal, the navball follows the camera, not the Kerbal.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/m7bgDuRiU4s?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible to make the navball follow the Kerbal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-06T17:37:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI see what you are talking about. \u00A0No idea, I\u0027ll look into it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sebra","CreatedById":174461,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-11T06:39:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi again!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to use LeftAlt \u002B W/S/A/D instead of Alpha2, X, Z, C. Is it possible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I try to change Orbit/Surface, mouse click goes through the Navball and select other ship/Kerbal. Can it be fixed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems you do not like my \u0022Space brakes\u0022 idea. Should I count it as discarded? ;-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-11T06:44:40Z\u0022 title=\u002203/11/2017 06:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Sebra\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-11T15:20:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222982398\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489214390\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sebra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Sebra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi again!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to use LeftAlt \u002B W/S/A/D instead of Alpha2, X, Z, C. Is it possible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I try to change Orbit/Surface, mouse click goes through the Navball and select other ship/Kerbal. Can it be fixed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems you do not like my \u0022Space brakes\u0022 idea. Should I count it as discarded? ;-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E for the key changing:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EI have found these work well in conjunction with the standard WASDQE controls (while letting you keep your right hand on the mouse for camera control). If you wish to remap them you can use the \u0022Settings\u0022 window, accessible from the stock application launcher or Blizzy78\u0027s toolbar.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe clickthrough is a KSP bug, nothing I can do about that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRe. the space brakes, if you want to code it, I\u0027ll most likely merge it. \u00A0But nothing I\u0027m going to do about it right now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sebra","CreatedById":174461,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-11T15:25:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI cannot change controls to Alt\u002BKey In \u0022Settings\u0022. It\u0027s looks like it is impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T12:42:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222977640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488821547\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Teilnehmer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/6/2017 at 0:32 PM, Teilnehmer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly. I experience the same navball behavior as in stock:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nWhen controlling a vessel, the navball doesn\u2019t follow the camera. It follows the vessel.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBut when controlling a Kerbal, the navball follows the camera, not the Kerbal.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible to make the navball follow the Kerbal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is actually a KSP bug (confirmed by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257146\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sarbian\u003C/a\u003E), or quirk, if you like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a fix for it, will get out an update with it later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T13:27:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew release, 0.1.7:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0Added fix to allow Navball follow kerbal on EVA\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0Added navball fix to settings screen\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0Updated toggle settings to be consistent with other settings\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Svm420","CreatedById":136047,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T17:22:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222983344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489322579\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is actually a KSP bug (confirmed by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257146\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sarbian\u003C/a\u003E), or quirk, if you like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a fix for it, will get out an update with it later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems weird\u00A0to call it a bug when it was\u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/1.0.5\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E a feature for the 1.0.5 update\u003C/a\u003E. Look under the navball\u00A0header. For the record, I am glad you fixed squads \u0022mistake\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-12T17:22:19Z\u0022 title=\u002203/12/2017 05:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 12, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Svm420\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T17:24:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222983533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489339326\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022136047\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Svm420\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Svm420 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems weird\u00A0to call it a bug when it was\u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/1.0.5\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E a feature for the 1.0.5 update\u003C/a\u003E. Look under the navball\u00A0header. For the record, I am glad you fixed squads \u0022mistake\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u0