uote-timestamp=\u00221489339442\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting. \u00A0So now you can have it both ways \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith both settings NavBall follows camera, not Kerbal. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T18:54:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222983589\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489344545\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sebra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Sebra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith both settings NavBall follows camera, not Kerbal. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease uninstall it, delete the directory, restart \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E and reinstall it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVerify the correct version by looking at the .version file in the directory\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just installed it via \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E again, had a problem so had to do what I just listed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it still isnt\u0027 working, log file and video, please\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sebra","CreatedById":174461,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T19:05:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUninstalled, deleted, restarted, reinstalled. Now it works well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut when it did not work, it still has that setting in settings. So it cannot be previous version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunniest part is NavBall wobbling like Kerbal head while he walks. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T19:16:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222983605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489345518\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sebra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Sebra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUninstalled, deleted, restarted, reinstalled. Now it works well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut when it did not work, it still has that setting in settings. So it cannot be previous version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunniest part is NavBall wobbling like Kerbal head while he walks. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nstrange, must have been something left over. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad it\u0027s working, thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sebra","CreatedById":174461,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T18:26:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShould NavBall show directions for Kerbals? Prograde and such...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt do not show them down on Kerbin.\u00A0 But on orbit they move with camera, not with Kerbal!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso NavBall HUD mod shows \u0022front\u0022 direction for Kerbal, pointed down, where his feets. (just for info).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow the EVA \u0022rotate on camera move\u0022 should work? I turn it on (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E on as well) and Kerbal do not rotate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso attempt to use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E control by mouse give error for Engineer and Scientist, but Pilot get \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E status (shown by NavBall HUD), even if \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E control remain not lit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-13T18:49:48Z\u0022 title=\u002203/13/2017 06:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 13, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Sebra\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-14T02:05:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll add an option to hide the markers while on EVA, but I can\u0027t totally recreate the Navball, there is too much hidden code.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984390\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489429606\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sebra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Sebra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso attempt to use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E control by mouse give error for Engineer and Scientist, but Pilot get \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E status (shown by NavBall HUD), even if \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E control remain not lit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease explain, i don\u0027t see any errors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984390\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489429606\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sebra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Sebra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt do not show them down on Kerbin.\u00A0 But on orbit they move with camera, not with Kerbal!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, in orbit, they show the correct location since the kerbal is in orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-14T13:37:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984390\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489429606\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sebra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, Sebra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow the EVA \u0022rotate on camera move\u0022 should work? I turn it on (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E on as well) and Kerbal do not rotate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso attempt to use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E control by mouse give error for Engineer and Scientist, but Pilot get \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E status (shown by NavBall HUD), even if \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E control remain not lit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/174461-sebra/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022174461\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/174461-sebra/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sebra\u003C/a\u003E Please explain what you are referring to, please.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat EVA \u0022rotate on camera move\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m holding up the next release with the option to disable the NavHud markers until this evening, if you can explain the error, I\u0027d like to fix it before releasing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"danielboro","CreatedById":166078,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-14T15:10:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222983344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489322579\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12.3.2017 at 2:42 PM, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is actually a KSP bug (confirmed by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257146\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sarbian\u003C/a\u003E), or quirk, if you like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a fix for it, will get out an update with it later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222977640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488821547\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Teilnehmer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6.3.2017 at 7:32 PM, Teilnehmer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly. I experience the same navball behavior as in stock:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nWhen controlling a vessel, the navball doesn\u2019t follow the camera. It follows the vessel.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBut when controlling a Kerbal, the navball follows the camera, not the Kerbal.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis is not a bug but works as intended\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis was mentioned in a vid of 1.0x relish promo as a new\u00A0 enhancement of the kerbal UI\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-14T15:10:45Z\u0022 title=\u002203/14/2017 03:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 14, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by danielboro\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-14T15:11:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222985136\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489504215\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166078\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022danielboro\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, danielboro said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis is not a bug but works as intended\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis was mentioned in a vid of 1.0x relish promo as an enhancement of the kerbal UI\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand I mentioned this in an earlier post: \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149997-12-eva-enhancements-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2983537\u0026amp;embedComment=2983537\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, the current developers seem to have a different way of looking at things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sebra","CreatedById":174461,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-14T15:13:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984818\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489457156\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984390\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489429606\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sebra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, Sebra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso attempt to use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E control by mouse give error for Engineer and Scientist, but Pilot get \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E status (shown by NavBall HUD), even if \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E control remain not lit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease explain, i don\u0027t see any errors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tm1YjvS.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/tm1YjvS.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022960\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch1\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECannot enable \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on non pilot Kerbal. It can be not related to your mod, just looks weird.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/h1\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984818\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489457156\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, in orbit, they show the correct location since the kerbal is in orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey show correct locations if NavBall follows the camera. If NavBall follows Kerbal, pointers still follows the camera.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNavBall HUD is on to show real pointers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00227ICkesd.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/7ICkesd.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022960\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}